The standard(?) way of checking if a service is running on Linux RHEL6 is not supported. I.e. the start/stop script does not support the "status" argument.
{code}
service atlstash status
Usage: /etc/init.d/atlstash {start|stop}
{code}

I would expect to see something like this:
{code}
service atlstash status
atlstash (pid  1158) is running...
{code}

